  <summary date="2019-08-02T10:34:44Z" status="Introduced in House">Patient Right to Know Drug Prices Act

This bill prohibits a health insurance plan or pharmacy benefits manager from restricting a pharmacy from informing an enrollee of any difference between the cost of a drug under the plan and the cost of the drug without health insurance coverage. (Such restrictions are commonly referred to as gag clauses.)</summary>
